{"title":"New Project One Colors for Trek Bikes Now Made with Low-Impact Pigments","link":"https://bikerumor.com/new-project-one-colors-trek-bikes-made-with-low-impact-pigments/","date":1742397637000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Trek-New-Environoxide-Paint-hero.webp\" width=\"1280\" height=\"720\" alt=\"(Photos / Trek Bikes)\" /></p>\n<p>Trek Bicycles is expanding its Project One Signature paint collection yet again. This time, Trek is featuring three new colorways using EnvironOxide. The new Moondust, Desert Muave, and Mojave Red colorways are the latest in Project One colors using environmentally preferred paint pigments. And, they are created with iron that’s been removed from polluted waterways.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Trek-New-Environoxide-Paint-first-pic-e1742323274589.webp\"><img width=\"1033\" height=\"563\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Trek-New-Environoxide-Paint-first-pic-e1742323274589.webp\" alt=\"Trek New Environoxide Paint first pic\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Trek-New-Environoxide-Paint-first-pic-e1742323274589.webp 1033w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Trek-New-Environoxide-Paint-first-pic-e1742323274589-297x162.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Trek-New-Environoxide-Paint-first-pic-e1742323274589-120x65.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Trek-New-Environoxide-Paint-first-pic-e1742323274589-768x419.webp 768w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photos / Trek Bikes)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The team over at Trek’s Project One created these new colors in conjunction with <a href=\"https://www.environoxide.com/vision.html\" target=\"_blank\">Oxide Recovery Inc.</a> Oxide Recovery removes and recovers excess iron from contaminated waterways from coal mining drainage to help create a range of products – like paint pigments. The process helps clean community waterways but also reduces mining for raw iron oxide materials that are traditionally used in creating paint pigments.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Trek-New-Environoxide-Paint-head-tube.webp\"><img width=\"1138\" height=\"1280\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Trek-New-Environoxide-Paint-head-tube.webp\" alt=\"Trek New Environoxide Paint head tube\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Trek-New-Environoxide-Paint-head-tube.webp 1138w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Trek-New-Environoxide-Paint-head-tube-267x300.webp 267w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Trek-New-Environoxide-Paint-head-tube-107x120.webp 107w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Trek-New-Environoxide-Paint-head-tube-768x864.webp 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Although low-impact paints amount to a small win for Trek’s overall sustainability efforts, they do shed light on the bigger shift that Trek is making toward a more sustainable future. Tip-o-the hat to ya, Trek Bikes! </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Trek-New-Environoxide-Paint-top-tube.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"720\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Trek-New-Environoxide-Paint-top-tube.webp\" alt=\"Trek New Environoxide Paint top tube\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Trek-New-Environoxide-Paint-top-tube.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Trek-New-Environoxide-Paint-top-tube-297x167.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Trek-New-Environoxide-Paint-top-tube-120x68.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Trek-New-Environoxide-Paint-top-tube-768x432.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Trek-New-Environoxide-Paint-top-tube-1200x675.webp 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>With the addition of these three new colors, Trek customers now have a choice of four EnviroOxide colorways to choose from when building their dream Project One Trek. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Trek-New-Environoxide-Paint-Moondust.webp\"><img width=\"740\" height=\"556\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Trek-New-Environoxide-Paint-Moondust.webp\" alt=\"Trek New Environoxide Paint Moondust\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Trek-New-Environoxide-Paint-Moondust.webp 740w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Trek-New-Environoxide-Paint-Moondust-297x223.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Trek-New-Environoxide-Paint-Moondust-120x90.webp 120w\" /></a><figcaption>Moodust</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Trek-New-Environoxide-Paint-desert-muave.webp\"><img width=\"740\" height=\"556\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Trek-New-Environoxide-Paint-desert-muave.webp\" alt=\"Trek New Environoxide Paint desert muave\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Trek-New-Environoxide-Paint-desert-muave.webp 740w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Trek-New-Environoxide-Paint-desert-muave-297x223.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Trek-New-Environoxide-Paint-desert-muave-120x90.webp 120w\" /></a><figcaption>Desert Muave</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Trek-New-Environoxide-Paint-Mojave-Red.webp\"><img width=\"740\" height=\"556\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Trek-New-Environoxide-Paint-Mojave-Red.webp\" alt=\"Trek New Environoxide Paint Mojave Red\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Trek-New-Environoxide-Paint-Mojave-Red.webp 740w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Trek-New-Environoxide-Paint-Mojave-Red-297x223.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Trek-New-Environoxide-Paint-Mojave-Red-120x90.webp 120w\" /></a><figcaption>Mojave Red</figcaption></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Raw Lithos, which was launched in 2024 with the all-new Checkmate SLR (and only available for that bike), is inspired by off-road, desert terrain. The all-new Moondust was inspired by off-white “lunar landscapes”. Desert Mauve embraces gray and purple geological hues, and Mojave Red embraces shades of red, orange, and brown. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Trek-New-Environoxide-Paint-full-bike.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"720\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Trek-New-Environoxide-Paint-full-bike.webp\" alt=\"Trek New Environoxide Paint full bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Trek-New-Environoxide-Paint-full-bike.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Trek-New-Environoxide-Paint-full-bike-297x167.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Trek-New-Environoxide-Paint-full-bike-120x68.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Trek-New-Environoxide-Paint-full-bike-768x432.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Trek-New-Environoxide-Paint-full-bike-1200x675.webp 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The new colors are now available on all Trek premium road bike models through Project One. Riders can customize their dream ride at Trek retailers around the world and online at the link below.  </p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.trekbikes.com/us/en_US/\" target=\"_blank\">TrekBikes.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/new-project-one-colors-trek-bikes-made-with-low-impact-pigments/\">New Project One Colors for Trek Bikes Now Made with Low-Impact Pigments</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Ron Frazelle","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"8bbd6b5f78c58e18af388b69c818839279b5aa515962a986f3e9962f71389c7d","category":"Cycling"}